projectInfo.name: Missing Maps: Buildings and residential areas, South of Madagascar (13)
projectInfo.shortDescription: In the South of Madagascar, a critical hunger situation is unfolding due to several years of dryness. The data will help MSF identify where people live to be able to evaluate needs, explore options for a future project and plan activities supporting them.
projectInfo.description:
In the South of Madagascar, a critical hunger situation is unfolding due to several years of dryness. The data will help MSF identify where people live to be able to evaluate needs, explore options for a future project and plan activities supporting them.

Because we noticed data gaps in the area,this task was set up to complete the data mapped earlier. The task was generated with help of [GRID3 settlement data](https://data.humdata.org/dataset/grid3-madagascar-settlement-extents-version-01-01) of Madagascar, leaving out the areas that are already covered in previous tasks.
projectInfo.instructions:
Imagery
========================
Please use **Maxar Premium** to do your mapping because it is the best imagery available. 

Buildings
========================
Please map all buildings. Buildings are generally squared and round huts with straw or tin roofs. They are **sometimes not easy to spot**, so please scan the area very carefully.  

**For rectangular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw an area and label it as *Building*”, then correct for right angles with the **Q** key.
* In JOSM: draw an area and use the tag *building=yes*, then correct for right angles using the **Q** key - OR use the building plugin.

**For circular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw a triangular area over the building and use the tag *Building*, then correct to make the shape circular with the **O** key.
* In JOSM: draw a line on the diameter of the building and use the tag *building=yes*; then hit **Shift + O** to make the shape circular – OR use one of the building/mapathoner plugins.

**Most buildings are rectangular** - So make buildings rectangular even if a shadow, tree or roof pitch make it appear otherwise. 

Residential areas 
========================= 

Please map all residential areas: a residential area is an inhabited area with **more than five (5) buildings closely clustered together**. 

* In iD: draw an **area** and mark as *Landuse Features=Residential Areas* 

* In JOSM: draw and **area** and mark as *landuse=residential* 

If a residential area shape already exists but does not encompass all the buildings in the village or town, please adjust the boundary accordingly. 

Mapping hints for mapping residential areas
========================= 

- A residential area is an area with more than five (5) buildings, but do not draw a residential area around every four buildings you map. Please, do zoom out and consider the right size of the residential area you are mapping.  

- The boundary of the residential area needs to be closed. Make sure that the start point of the line, joins to the end point.  

- The line for the residential area you draw can cross highways, buildings, streams, etc. but should not share any points or lines with them.  

- If your residential area is bigger than your selected area, draw a closed area as good as you can, and *hand it over* by placing the boundary of the area just outside your area so the next mapper can take it on from there. 

- Don’t confuse residential areas with farmland!
